OSES = ONE Software Engineering System, Siemens internal developer platform.

## Domains
1. Cloud Operations — Archival, Cloud Security, Incident Response, Observability
2. Delivery & Hosting — Cloud Modeling/Runtime/Compute/Delivery, Desktop/Edge delivery, AI Development
3. Development & CI — Artifacts mgmt, Development Plane, Static Validation
4. Plan & Design — ALM (Architecture, UX Design), Catalog (Asset Management)
5. Platform Services — Control Plane (GitOps), External/Internal Developer Portal

## Releases (quarterly)
- OSES.1 (Q3 2025) — Initial release. 7 use cases: app registration, software catalog, Python paved path, UCP, shared compute onboarding, cloud account ordering, Faros AI productivity.
- OSES.2 (Q4 2025) — 5 use cases: brownfield visibility, GPU on-demand, K8s self-service, package security blocking, image signing enforcement. Plus UCP enhancements, Backstage UX, AWS Bedrock.
- OSES.3 (Q1 2026) — 5 use cases: dual APM monitoring, ingress migration (NGINX→successor), EFS shared storage, IRSA cert-manager, Policy-as-Code (OPA/Kyverno).

